
Color format -

E.g. - Hex value 
     #43A322

Q. - Why directly not write color name i.e. blue or other color name?
==>
  - Problem with blue write directly place of hex value interpretation in Mozilla firefox are work different & Chrome have different.
  - Its professional way to write color in hex value.

For view any HSL values & RGB values of color -
  - Hover on hex value color & click on hex value  

hsl ==> Hue, Saturation, and Light.
    E.g. hsl(178, 86%, 41%);
	
rgba ==> Red, Green, Blue, alpha channel
    E.g. rgb(15, 196, 190, .5);


Different ways of introducing style -
1] Head tag
2] Inline tag inject style through Attribute
3] Style in seperate file ( it link in main file header)

*NOTE :-
This in line type styling useful when, conditionally time rendering. 
- i.e. when user can login its show green button, when its not login show red button 
- This time In line style are more helpful.

E.g. -
<h3 style="
      text-align:center;
      background-color: rgba(15, 196, 190, .5);
      color: blueviolet;
</h3>

*NOTE :- Inline tag most used for React / Angular learning.


Quotes OR Quoatation - (try to learn from documentation)

Problem with <q> tag -
 - Less time use of <q> , because its automatically inject block quotes
 E.g. -
    <q>
	   this is my quotes
	</q>
 
 ==> "this is my quotes"
 
 - Best way to inject quote through CSS. i.e. CSS property called before & after 
 - Inject quotes better through CSS.

abbrevation tag -
E.g. -
    <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup language">HTML</abbr>

Assignment :- Search in documentation like - Address html mdn

addresss tag -
- This element only includes the global attributes.
E.g. -
    <address>
      <a href="mailto:jim@example.com">jim@example.com</a><br />
      <a href="tel:+14155550132">+1 (415) 555‑0132</a>
    </address> 
	
cite tag - The Citation element
- <cite> element in italics by default. To avoid this, apply the CSS font-style property to the <cite> element.
E.g. -
    <p>More information can be found in <cite>[ISO-0000]</cite>.</p>

bdo tag - Bidirectional Text Override element 
- The <bdo> html element overrides the current directionality of text.
E.g. -
    <bdo dir="rtl">Swapnil</bdo>
 
 
 E.g. -
 
 
 <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <style>
            body{
                  color: aqua;
            }
      </style>
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
      <title>Formatting</title>
</head>
<body>
      <!-- <h1>Formatting</h1> -->
      <h1>Formatting</h1>
      <h1>Formatting</h1>

      <!-- Bold in html head vs paragraph -->
      <h3> this is <b>important</b> </h3>

      <hr>
      <!-- strong tag vs bold tag -->
      <p> this is <b>important</b> </p>
      <p> this is <strong>important</strong> </p>

      <hr>
      <!-- strong tag vs bold tag -->
      <p>this is <i>important</i> </p>
      <p>this is <em>important</em> </p>

      <hr />
      <hr />
      <p><strong>Assignment</strong> Task - </p>
      <!-- aliase 4 bullet points ==> ul>li*4 -->
      <ul>
            <li>b; string</li>
            <li>i; em</li>
            <li>small</li>
            <li>sub, sup</li>
            <li>del, mark</li>
      </ul>


      <!-- sub tag subscript -->
      <p> H <sub>2</sub> 0 </p>
      <!-- sup tag superscript -->
      <p>a<sup>2</sup> +b<sup>2</sup>=c<sup>2</sup></p>

      <!-- Style attribute in multiple properties -->
      <h3 style="
      text-align:center;
      background-color: rgba(15, 196, 190, .5);
      color: blueviolet;

      " >This tag needs some styling</h3>

      <p>
            <q>
                  this is my quote
            </q>

            <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup language">HTML</abbr>
      </p>

